            },
            "answer_text": "Yes. See how easy that was? It depends, however, on how you define a sentence. I prefer: a statement that expresses a complete thought. The reason the single word yes can express a complete thought is that it is always a response, and there is an implied subject and verb that reflect the question the yes responds to. So my yes above is simply a short form for: Yes, it is.This is a common structure in a question and response pair. The question normally includes an interrogative adverb plus a subject and verb. The response is a matching adverb, like yes, or an equivalent adjective, like sure, without the subject and verb since it supplied implicitly by the question. Really, is that all there is to it? Yes, really. ",
